text: The Selimiye Mosque (Turkish: Selimiye Camii) is an Ottoman imperial mosque, which is in Edirne, Turkey. The mosque was commissioned by Sultan Selim II, and was built by architect Mimar Sinan between 1569 and 1575. == References == Category:World Heritage Sites in Turkey Category:Mosques in Turkey Category:16th-century buildings and structures Category:Edirne Province
title: Selimiye Mosque
